what it is: a function inside roblox that takes the scriptcontext instance and returns the main lua_State
(aka the main thread where all the lua globals and environment stuff live)

what its used for: this is basically the main part of execution. u cant run scripts without a lua state. since roblox hides the main state inside the 
ScriptContext
(which u grab from the datamodel), u gotta call this function to extract it

how u use it: u pass it the scriptcontext pointer (plus a couple dummy pointers for identity and script that it fills out) and it gives you lua_State* once u got that
u spawn ur own child thread off of it and use that child thread to compile and run ur custom scripts without crashing the main game


HOW TO GET IT 🤑
// finding GetGlobalState offset in ida:
// 1. search for the string "Script Start" and go to its first xref
// 2. look for a line assigning the string like this: *(_QWORD *)(ScriptVMState + 256) = "Script Start";
// 3. that `ScriptVMState` comes from L->userdata->Shared->ScriptVMState
// 4. trace how `ScriptVMState` gets passed by following the variables upwards until u find the underlying `lua_State` (L)
// 5. u will see some decryption math and a function call right before it
// 6. look at the xrefs for THAT specific function u found, and that function address is ur GetGlobalState offset
